<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn48">  48  The Prankquean tale seems in part to embody a Viconian version of the evolution of language from the inarticulate grunts and whines of the inexpressive giants, save when under the influence of great passion (Shit!), with the first words being loud and onomatopoeic utterances. The first language would have been, on this view, a kind of poetic, creative singing.  </div>
